Title : Portal:Current events/2014 May 4
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|05|04}}

; Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]]
**Pro-Russian activists attack the police headquarters in [[Odessa]], forcing the release of several people held over deadly violence two days before. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-27276120 (BBC)]

;Disasters and accidents
*The [[Government of Afghanistan]] declares a day of national mourning for the victims of [[2014 Badakhshan mudslides|the mudslides]]. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-27273684 (BBC)]
*At least eleven people die in [[People's Republic of China|China's]] [[Guangdong Province]] when a bridge collapses while being built. [http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/13-people-killed-in-bridge-house-collapse-in-china-114050400292_1.html (PTI via Business Standard)]
*A train [[derailment]] in the [[Raigad district]] of [[India]]'s [[Maharashtra]] state causes at least 19 deaths and 130 people injured. [https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/05/04/us-india-train-idUSBREA4307Q20140504 (Reuters)]

;Law and crime
*[[Murder of Jean McConville]] and [[Arrest of Gerry Adams]]:
**Northern Ireland's First Minister [[Peter Robinson (Northern Ireland politician)|Peter Robinson]] accuses [[Sinn Féin]] of attempting to blackmail the [[Police Service of Northern Ireland]] over the arrest of [[Gerry Adams]]. [http://www.rte.ie/news/2014/0504/615151-gerry-adams-psni/ (RTE News)]
**Sinn Féin President Gerry Adams is released from police custody after four days of questioning over the murder of Jean McConville. [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-27278039 (BBC)]

;Politics
*''[[The Sunday Herald]]'' becomes the first Scottish newspaper to declare its support for a Yes vote in the forthcoming [[2014 Scottish independence referendum|referendum on Scottish independence]]. [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-27274460 (BBC)]
*[[Panamanian general election, 2014]]
**Voters in [[Panama]] go to the polls for a general election. [http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/politics/2014/05/04/panama-holds-presidential-election/ (Fox News Latino)]
**Current [[Vice President of Panama|Vice President]] [[Juan Carlos Varela]] wins the Presidential election. [http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/3d281c11a96b4ad082fe88aa0db04305/Article_2014-05-04-Panama-Presidential%20Election/id-f8fc42f613ec47418e47d95b84b55f9c (AP)]

